(88, 91, 'PHLISSA HUB Prototype', 1312257600, 1313035200, 1335758400, 4, 'The goal for this stage of the project is to migrate the Hub from a development environment into the CDC R&D Lab and verify that the Hub solution can be successfully deployed using the implementation guides and consultant support and that data exchange via HL7 messaging can be demonstrated with the newly installed product.  \r\n', 'No', 'Prototype', 'External'),
(89, 92, 'PHIFP - Community Health Record', 1312257600, 1333166400, 1370232000, 1, 'The aim of the project is to explore the development of a geographically based community health record for public health decision support. The specific aims, objectives, and details of the project are still being developed as I am a new Public Health Informatics Fellow. We request the use of the lab to explore a variety of software packages available for visual informatics, to develop a mock-up and prototype of our dashboard concept to garner higher level support. As it is geographically based, I would also like to load a couple of GIS software packages to so that we can more easily work with various geospatial layers.  ', '', 'Evaluation', 'External'),
(90, 93, 'Mobile Applications (â€œappâ€) to Increase HIV Testing Behavior and HIV Prevention with Positive Persons', 1312257600, 1317355200, 1380513600, 0, 'The purpose of this project is to develop 2 innovative mobile applications â€œappsâ€ in support of HIV prevention: (1) an app for HIV-positive persons that provides HIV prevention information, including HIV treatment management, retention in care, and adherence assistance; and (2) an HIV testing app that provides basic HIV prevention information for high-risk HIV negative persons, regularly reminds users to get tested, and identifies nearby testing locations and HIV prevention resources.  There are two phases to this project: (1) formative research (FOA) and (2) app development (contract). The formative phase will be used to determine the needs and preferences of potential users in the two target populations (persons living with HIV and MSM at high risk for HIV infection) for the proposed types of mobile apps.  During the app development phase, a contractor will develop 2 apps (as described above) and accompanying Internet and mobile websites based on formative research findings.  \r\n\r\nWe would like to consult with the Informatics Research and Development Unit (IRDU) on the development of the app prototypes and the writing of the contract or task order for the app development.\r\n', '', 'Evaluation', 'External'),
