(170, 173, 'SMART PHONE EXPOSURE ASSESSMENT RESCUER (SPEAR)', 1359435600, 1359435600, 1372564800, 1, 'This engagement request is for preliminary work towards writing a full project proposal.  This preliminary work will develop simple Android apps to demonstrate the concept â€“ no personal identifying information.  The follow on project will use smart phones to gather, process, log, and forward exposure assessment data, and these phones may also automatically text alerts if exposure becomes hazardous. The full project will be divided into four phases:\r\n1.	 Program and verify performance for the available input/output ports on selected devices, \r\n2.	write a universal app,\r\n3.	design and build sensor modules, and\r\n4.	test a functional prototype.  \r\nPhase 3 may network several of these instruments together into a common database for monitoring.  \r\nPhase 4 will field test the instruments and the network.  \r\nThe follow on project will take 2 to 3 years.  \r\n', 'No', 'Prototype', 'External'),
