(72, 69, 'Renewed as Engagement #150 for six months.\r\n\r\nEmailed Joshua Jesko for feedback 5/9/12. [BAL]\r\nEmailed Josh Jesko / Kiran Katragadda requesting new engagement form on 8/29/12. [BAL]\r\n\r\nResults sent in by Cas Pallansch on 8/31, new engagement form processed as #150: [BAL]\r\n-	Received and deployed several test builds of the Mobile Framework Services components that ultimately allowed us to get the software through a user acceptance testing milestone earlier this year.  This acceptance was necessary before initiating the process of getting the components installed in the CDC production environments (which v1.0.0 of MFS now has been).\r\n-	Associated with the successful deployment of the MFS into a CDC production environment, we were able to submit and received acceptance of our first Mobile Framework-based iOS mobile app to the Apple Store (we have several iOS apps in the store, but this was the first one based on this framework).\r\n-	EMB has recently submitted iOS mobile apps for other content/topic areas within CDC that include MMWR and PCD.  Other instances that are in progress include an app for Flu and ATSDR.\r\n-	EMB is working with the FDA on an instance of a MFS-based mobile app that makes use the MFS instance in the Informatics Lab (this is really the only non-production, external-facing mechanism we have for testing with the FDA).\r\n\r\nMoving forward, I believe the plan is to wrap up the currently identified set of iOS-based mobile applications that use the MFS and get them submitted to the Apple Store.  We will continue to work with the FDA on the current application along with possibly other applications that they identify during the course of the next fiscal year.\r\n', ''),
