(75, 72, 'We found that the developers work more efficiently when they are in the same work space vs. being remote. Our developers normally work remote from Massachusetts and Virginia.\r\n\r\nFrom the assistance of working with Tom and the Research and Development Laboratory that he manages, we were able to do the following:\r\nï¿½	Created a ï¿½war roomï¿½ ï¿½ where we had our remote developers travel to Century Center for the  purpose of creating a rapid development environment.\r\nï¿½	Performed development outside of the CDC network ï¿½ we have a current problem where we cannot access the vendorï¿½s VPN because the CDC firewall blocks access to the port that would allow entry. The R&D lab is one of the few places within the CDC campuses where our developers could come together and perform development outside of the CDC network.\r\nï¿½	Provided an environment of knowledge sharing ï¿½ this would not have happened if the resources were not together and could not look over each otherï¿½s shoulder.\r\nï¿½	Survived initial technical difficulties ï¿½ the first morning we had difficulties getting into the vendorï¿½s VPN, but Tom and Dale provided our team with excellent technical support. By later that morning we were able to get past our connection problems. \r\n\r\n', ''),
