(92, 89, 'renewed for another 3 months on March 4, 2013\r\n\r\nPer EMAIL===========\r\nWith regard to my request for continued use of Confluence for the CHR project, I have summarized the use of the wiki for the CHR below.  \r\n\r\nThe Memphis Community Health Record project is utilizing Confluence to facilitate collaboration, communication and content development and sharing among its local, state and national stakeholders.  This project wiki went live in January 2013 and it is currently utilized by all 27 project members: 17 individuals at the local level, two individuals at the state level and eight individuals at the national level.  Two of the individuals at the local level were granted access to the project wiki during the preceding two month access period.  Additionally, the project team began utilizing Confluence for document development and sharing and project communication.  This service is essential to the CHR project and collaboration of such diverse community health stake holders.  We would like to request an additional three to six months of access and access renewal for at least the next two years. \r\n======================\r\n\r\n', ''),
