(125, 122, 'Appendix A â€“ Memorandum of Understanding\r\nIRDA will work with its TSE to obtain and manage the following equipment for use during this engagement:\r\n2 Apple New iPad 32GB Wifi-only (serial numbers=DMQHTCCCDJ8R, DMQHTDW7DJ8R)\r\n2 Apple Applecare support licenses\r\n2 ASUS Transformer Pad TF300T Tablets\r\n2 ASUS TF300 Docking Stations\r\n\r\nThe cost of this equipment is estimated at $2,380.78 (quote attached) but the precise amount will vary depending on PGOâ€™s sourcing of the equipment.\r\n\r\nNCEH / ATSDR will provide a CAN and authorize its use by IRDA to acquire this equipment.\r\n\r\nIRDA will retain all equipment, serve as the steward of this equipment, and manage it in accordance with CDCâ€™s asset tracking procedures.\r\n\r\nIRDA will provide this equipment to NCEH / ATSDR for purposes described above in this document for a limited duration of time. Use of this equipment should only be conducted under the rules of behavior contained within the R&D Lab Security Policy and at no time should connect to the CDC network, nor contain any sensitive data, nor connect to any production systems.\r\n\r\nShould CDC ITSO and OCISO policy change to approve this equipment for production use within the agency, IRDA will work with IRDA and NCEH TSEs to transfer the equipment from IRDA to NCEH.\r\n\r\nThe project points of contact are: Tom Savel, MD for IRDA and Lawrence Furphy for NCEH/ATSDR.\r\n\r\n\r\n2 Apple New Black iPad 32GB Wifi-only (barcodes) 225727 (serial#=DMQHTCCCDJ8R) and 225719 (serial#=DMQHTDW7DJ8R)\r\n2 Apple Applecare support licenses\r\n2 ASUS Transformer Pad TF300T Tablets (barcodes) 225722 and 225721\r\n2 ASUS TF300 Docking Stations (S/N) C4OKCT083015 and C4OKCT083013', ''),
