(136, 133, 'iPad loaned to Sam Posner, Serial Number=GB051N50ETUl Wifi MAC=10:93:E9:21:E6:3E; Model=MC496LL\r\niPad returned to Tom on 9/12. Testing was completed successfully and Posner will submit app to OADC for publication to app store.\r\n\r\nPer Kim Bright:  The loaned iPad was extremely helpful to themâ€¦ in testing the appâ€¦and ultimately getting their app submitted to OADC.\r\n\r\nremoved from our notification DB by Savel.\r\n\r\nFeedback email received from Kim Bright on 9/18:\r\nHi all,\r\n\r\nGreat news!  The PCD iPad app has been approved by Apple and is now live in the app store/iTunes.  After 8 months of development, QA, collaborations, graphics prep, and a few delays along the way, our app is finally available to our readers, researchers, practitioners, policy makers, and the general public with an interest in public health efforts to prevent chronic disease.\r\n\r\nThere have been many boots on the ground to bring this app to fruition.  We appreciate the team effort and contributions of all involved, with special thanks to:\r\n\r\nâ€¢	Alexis Simmons, who helped kick-off the project with content for our information architecture and graphics selections.\r\nâ€¢	Kristen Immoor, for content clean-up and hours of graphic design to make sure our app images meet usability and Apple, Inc. requirements.\r\nâ€¢	Ansel Floy (Security Steward) and Cindy Allen (ISSO), for their assistance in guiding us through OCISO security documentation and approval.\r\nâ€¢	The OADC Mobile and Syndication teams (Alex, Cass, Sharon, Kiran, Nina), for their guidance, collaboration, and leadership in taking our app from concept to production.\r\nâ€¢	Tom Savel and the R&D lab for the iPad device loaner to get us through Dev and QA.\r\nâ€¢	Scott Brittain for consistent OIIRM support and site management.\r\nâ€¢	PCD leadership and team who work their magic everyday to further the success of our journal!\r\n\r\nBe sure to tell your friends and colleagues with iPads or iPhones to download the app and let us know how weâ€™re doing (rate us or comment).  Now shifting focus to app maintenance and promotionsâ€¦\r\n', ''),
