(143, 140, 'Installed Visual Studio 2010 Premium - since no specific version was indicated. \r\n\r\nRenewed for another cycle today  - 2/5/13\r\n\r\nUpdate as of 2/5/13 - Duane Jones:\r\nWe were able to successfully develop an initial prototype/pilot application that includes reportable condition rules for 7 jurisdictions covering 3 reportable conditions (TB, Blood Lead and Pertussis). We demoâ€™d the app to our stakeholders who would like to move forward with a second phase pilot, which will introduce some further functionality. We were extended through June 30, 2013 to add an authoring mechanism, user profiles and human and machine readable reporting over the next few months. This will complete the pilot and demonstrate that the application has viability and value to public health and clinical providers nationwide to continue into a full implementation. During the next 4 months Laura Conn will be deciding upon the best method for continuing and funding the RCKMS project past the pilot stage and into a full production implementation. At this time, beginning July 1, 2013, we plan to move into AHB/SDN/DSS (whatever they are called now) for a full deployment.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', ''),
