(73, 71, 'In order to adequately archive OMS artifacts, the OMS executable, OMS documentation and OMS development environment will be stored on various medium. The virtualization process provides a mechanism/environment that stores all artifacts efficiently. The virtual environment provides an on-demand environment that is far easier to recreate than just an ordinary backup/restore environment. \r\n\r\nDue to the complex nature of the development environment and the mix of VB6, and .NET code, virtualizing will facilitate access of OMS artifacts. The virtualization process facilitates a key archive requirement of being to leverage OMS features for the Epi Info™ development. Included in the virtualization process would be an executable instance of OMS for demonstration purposes. Although the OMS artifacts require large amounts of disk space, retrieval of the various artifacts would only be as needed. \r\n\r\nOur Team is looking to virtualize our current subnet farm environment which is not connected to the CDC network. This virtualized environment would serve as a backup so that if there comes a point where OMS is to be brought back up, we can do so easily with minimal setup. \r\n\r\nOur farm consists of a Domain Controller, TESTLAB-SVR6 (Contains Databases, SharePoint, Team Foundation server), TESTLAB-SVR5 (Fileserver) and a build computer. We would be able create a VMware image for the VMware server version that is running in the lab using the VMware converter. Once the images are created, they can be copied over to the Lab server and may require some network configurations. This setup would be on its own network since it has its own domain controller. The virtual images would only serve as a backup, so they don’t need to be running 24/7. The resources required for the servers are as follows:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTESTLAB-SVR6\r\nServer 6 role(s):  SQL Database Server, TFS Server \r\nFull Name: TESTLAB-SVR6.epitestlab\r\nDomain: epitestlab\r\nC drive: 70GB\r\nE drive: 600GB\r\nMemory: 4GB\r\n\r\nTESTLAB-SVR5\r\nServer 5 role(s):  File Server \r\nFull Name: testlab-svr5.epitestlab\r\nDomain: epitestlab\r\nC drive: 20GB\r\nE drive: 125GB\r\nMemory:  2GB\r\n\r\nTESTLAB-DC1\r\nServer role(s): Domain Controller\r\nFull Name: testlab-dc1.epitestlab\r\nDomain: epitestlab\r\nC drive: 8GB\r\nMemory: 1GB\r\n\r\n\r\nD204016\r\nServer role(s): Build Computer\r\nFull Name: D204016.epitestlab\r\nDomain: epitestlab\r\nC drive: 150GB\r\nMemory: 2GB\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Users to have access to all VMs:\r\n\r\nTino Mowatt\r\nlec4@cdc.gov\r\n\r\nGerald Jones\r\ngfj0@cdc.gov\r\n\r\nZack Gao\r\npzg5@cdc.gov\r\n'),
