(70, 68, 'Iï¿½ll be using the environment diagram on this page: \r\n\r\nhttps://sites.google.com/site/dirddivision/software/environmentsforirduwebprojects \r\n\r\nas a reference for our desired end state. One day, we plan on having all this in place so we can efficiently and reliably update and code and content on RDLWP and our various demo projects.\r\n\r\nTo go live with our minimum features, we only need these four tasks to be complete:\r\n1)	SMTP - Dale\r\n2)	Staging VM ï¿½ Dale \r\n3)	RDLWP Configuration Document ï¿½ Sara\r\n4)	Live VM ï¿½ Dale\r\n\r\nIf all four things happen, then we can go live with RDLWP and Tom can guide the site through scientific clearance. Each of the four steps is described a bit below.\r\n\r\n1)	SMTP ï¿½ Dale sets up the capability to send email from RDLWP using SMTP.\r\n2)	Staging VMï¿½ Dale creates a ï¿½production levelï¿½ Linux host that will be a mirror image of our Live server (mentioned below). This is a minimal VM that only contains whatever administrative/security software, Apache2 with PHP5 and MySQL5.\r\n3)	RDLWP Configuration Document ï¿½ Sara documents all of the steps necessary to configure RDLWP on the Staging VM. Just a simple wiki page that talks about what tools (e.g., Joomla, media-wiki, plugins, etc.) are used, how to install them, how to configure them; and what content is required and where it comes from (e.g., SVN). This document will describe how to set up a new Joomla site fresh and will result in the Staging VM being a fully configured RDLWP.\r\n4)	Live VM ï¿½ Sara/Tom/Brian/Dale test out Staging and once we have consensus that it is properly functioning, Dale makes a copy of Staging and reconfigures it as our live server (e.g., external access, etc.)\r\n\r\nThatï¿½s it. When we complete #4, the site will be ï¿½liveï¿½.\r\n\r\nBased on priorities and timelines, Dale will set up the Content Staging and External Demo VMs. It is sub-optimal to go live without these two VMs, but it is possible.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
