(64, 62, 'The goal of the nomenclature project is to create a set of open source tools and an openly available, LS3PO curated knowledge base that enabled physicians to determine the applicability of lab test requests based on lab provider and initial diagnosis. These tools are designed to easily integrate into existing EMR products so that any existing computerized physician order entry (CPOE) processes can be extended and augmented using the knowledge base. This prototype will be developed in multiple phases using a quick, iterative approach to demonstrating functionality and revising based on stakeholder feedback.\r\n\r\nThe first phase will create a knowledge base (KB) hosted within the R&D lab and curated by LS3PO subject matter experts. The KB will link diagnosis concepts to specific tests as defined by each test provider (e.g., LabCorp, Quest). A light web api will allow partners to request lookups of specific tests by provider based on diagnosis. For example, a client would request all LabCorp tests for HyperTension and receive a result of the panel of tests that should be submitted. The initial prototype will focus on Thyroid and Vitamin D deficiency diagnoses, but will be expanded based on additional areas defined by LS3PO .A small demonstration app will be built to show off the capability of looking up the specific tests by provider based on diagnosis. If possible, this demonstration app will be built using the Substitutable Medical Apps, reusable technology (SMArt) framework to allow for easy integration into SMArt enabled EMRs and PHRs.\r\n\r\nThe second phase will extend KB functionality by mapping general lab test concepts to specific LOINC codes used by each test provider. This will allow suggestion of specific lab tests based on easy for the physician to enter test names and prevent the misentry of incorrect tests. The demonstration app will be updated to show off the test name concept expansion functionality. The second phase will also include curation tools that allow LS3PO to easily enter, update and maintain the KB.\r\n\r\nAdditional phases can be added to provide functionality based on community feedback and to more directly engage commercial EMR/PHR vendors on how to include Nomenclature functionality in their product sets.\r\n\r\nWhile data is curate by LS3PO it is non-proprietary and the entire data set can be periodically published to the LS3PO cdc.gov web site to allow for EMR/PHR vendors to use whole cloth, rather than accessing via the web api developed in phase 1.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(66, 64, 'GOAL: Faster approval for the implementation of new workstation-installed software for use by OSELS personnel\r\n\r\nCHALLENGES: Approval for new software used for the CDC LAN (Level III approval) requires an assertion by the vendor that this software does not impact the Federal Desktop Core Configuration mandatory settings for workstations. The vendor may be unwilling or unable to supply this.\r\n\r\nOPPORTUNITY CREATED: The FDCC can also be supplied by the ISSOs, if they can test software before asserting its suitability and compatibility with the FDCC. \r\n\r\nWHY THE LAB:  The testing requires installation of the un-approved software, which should not be performed on a CDC LAN system. If performed outside the lab, the ISSOs would use a single non-lab system that could not be connected to the CDC LAN, but would require updates and patches as any other system.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'access:\r\n\r\nAlison Gunnels    ddx3\r\nKeyaan Wiliams    kvw5\r\nReginald Hart     vgf4'),
(30, 28, 'It is estimated that over 50% of doctors own and use smart phones. This number is expected to increase to ~ 80% by 2013. In order to reach doctors and other health professional where they are, we would like to provide the 2010 STD treatment guidelines via a user friendly, smart phone application. The STD treatment guidelines are the authoritative source for treatment of STDs.', 'Offer the STD Treatment guidelines as a free application for smart phones in user friendly format', 'Healthcare personnel involved with sexual health (includes OB/GYNs)', 'first line workers for STD Prevention', 'STD clinic staff, GPs, pediatricians', '', 'CDC DSTDP', 'funders of STD prevention efforts', 'CDC OD', 'funders of STD prevention efforts', '', '', '', '', 'CDC STD Tx Guidelines', 'Not sure how to answer this.', 'Not sure how to answer this.', 'The Treatment guidelines will be released as a MMWR sometime in OCT/NOV 2010'),
