(31, 29, 'Notifying sex aprtners of patients with a diagnosed STD and/or HIV (partner notification/services) is a cornerstone of STD prevention. By notifying and testing known sex partners, the chain of transmission can be broken. The internet has created multiple challenges for conducting partner services. Often times patients will only have an email adress or online profile name for a sex partner. In order to notify sex partners of their exposure, STD disease intervention specialists (DIS) officers need access to sites on the internet. Often these sites are sexually explicit and as a result DIS officers are unable to access the sites due to firewalls, local policies and/or bureaucratic hurdles. We would like to develop a solution that will allow DIS to access sexually explicit sites in order to conduct partner services in such a way as to protect the servers they are working from, protect patient confidentiality, and so that the solution is acceptable to local and state governments.', 'Provide access to sexually explicit site to allow for STD prevention efforts such as partner notification, outreach and the provision of health information.', 'Field DIS Officers across the country', 'first line workers for STD Prevention', 'CDC DSTDP', 'funders of STD prevention efforts', 'CDC OD', 'funders of STD prevention efforts', 'Local & State Governments', 'Representatives of general public', '', '', '', '', 'n/a', 'not sure how to answer this', 'not sure how to answer this', 'Partner services via internet has been a hot button issue in the field of STD prevention for over 5 years. There are those that whole-heartedly support online prevention efforts and others who are adamantly opposed.'),
(27, 24, 'The federal government is now required to participate in the Geospatial Platform. The Geospatial Platform is a shared services framework across federal agencies. We need to set up a ArcGIS server, web services, and test what services we can potentially provide, illustrate to HHS the capability, and illustrate to the programs the benefit of sharing their data through this method. The challenges will be setting up the services and interface that will be the most useful to the Geospatial Platform, programs in CDC, and partners.', 'I would like to create an environment of services that can illustrate how we can share geospatial information across the federal and public health space. In addition, to show leadership how we can support the programs so that they ca enhance their efforts.', 'Federal Agencies', 'consumers and delivers of data for us to consume', 'CDC CIOs', 'consumers', 'Public Health Partners', 'consumers and potentially delivers of data for our programs to consume', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'GIS data but later in the production environment, NCHS and program data', '', '', 'The other key stakeholder is the Federal Geospatial Data Committee (FGDC) and their standards on how to share the services.'),
