(90, 88, 'The PHLISSA Hub is an Open Source Software (OSS) solution which has been developed as part of the CDCâ€™s Public Health Laboratory Interoperability Solutions and Solution Architecture (PHLISSA) project and is designed to broker information flows between the CDC, Public Health Labs, Clinical Care Stakeholders, and State/Local/Territorial Public Health Departments for use case scenarios involving meaningful use criteria.  The goal for this stage of the project is to migrate the Hub from a development environment into the CDC R&D Lab and verify that the Hub solution can be successfully deployed using the implementation guides and consultant support and that data exchange via HL7 messaging can be demonstrated with the newly installed product.  \r\nThe Hub is currently utilizing a number of message transport protocols, which include the Direct REST messaging and web services solution.  Additional discussion and planning will be required to determine if multiple iterations of the PHLISSA Hubs will need to be deployed in order to demonstrate the expected information flow exchange.   \r\nThe use of the R&D Lab will allow for the installation of two instances of the product in an external setting from the development environment in order to determine future deployment and â€œproduction hardeningâ€ requirements of the product prior to deployment in a pilot setting with clinical care/public health stakeholders\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Tech Backup point of contact:  Michael Trebatowski  Michael.J.Trebatoski@saic.com\r\nTech Backup point of contact:  Paul Dejong   Paul.R. Dejong@saic.com\r\nProgram Backup point of contact:  Tom Brinks   ble0@cdc.gov\r\n', 'Tech Backup point of contact:  Michael Trebatowski  Michael.J.Trebatoski@saic.com\r\nTech Backup point of contact:  Paul Dejong   Paul.R. Dejong@saic.com\r\nProgram Backup point of contact:  Tom Brinks   ble0@cdc.gov\r\n', 'Paul Dejong	PAUL.R.DEJONG@saic.com\r\nMike Eidson	MICHA