(93, 91, 'Currently, AIP has numerous legacy systems created in Corel Paradox and PowerBuilder.  These systems makeup what could essentially be labeled Epidemiology and Laboratory/Specimen Bank.  It appears that Corel does not have plans to update the software.  The current version is approximately ten years old.  Although PowerBuilder is still a viable solution, using a single technology is easier to support.  Now, with CDCâ€™s decision to move to Windows 7, and the fact that ITSO does not support Paradox, AIP has decided itâ€™s time to migrate.  The vision is for an umbrella application much like an intranet that would have three divisions, Administrative, Epidemiology and the Laboratory.  Migrating the entire operation is both a challenge and a huge opportunity to improve processes in an effort to work smarter in every area from data collection to lab testing to records management.  The primary application technology is the MS .Net framework and will probably include Asp.net using MVC, Entity framework, JavaScript and maybe some Silverlight.  The production application will reside on an IIS, with the backend database on a MSSQL server.  Using the lab to start development will expedite this project and provide the flexibility to try technologies without burdening ITSO or OCISO.\r\nThe R&D Lab resources will be used for prototyping and testing.  As clarity is obtained as to the stack to be used in this new infrastructure, code will be moved to a formal / dedicated development environment â€“ and, once a formal C&A is obtained, transitioned to production.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
