(132, 130, 'This project is to test the viability of the Samsung Galaxy tablet as a device for data collection internationally.  This will involve the procurement of test devices, the installation and testing of data collection tools, and the validation of battery life, screen visibility, and field specific device requirements.  At the end of the project we would make a decision whether to pursue this as a replacement device for our outdated platform.', '', 'CGH OD', 'Report recipient/governing body', 'CGH Divisions', 'Report recipient', 'DPDM statistics and information team', 'Users and data suppliers', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(138, 136, 'We aim to demonstrate that situational awareness and cognitive burden can be improved through improved information communication with miners (mine rescue teams, mine foreman, general miner, etc.). We plan to use an android-based application as an experimental mock-up to perform various experiments in mine rescue and mine emergency situations to prove this point and generate improved guidelines. The assistance of the lab is need to purchase a development phone.', '', 'United Mine Workers of America', 'Union for user body', 'MSHA', 'Governing Body', 'Mine Training Community', 'Users/report recipients', 'Mining Companies (i.e. Consol)', 'Users/report recipients', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(133, 131, 'FMO would like to test three 3rd party system monitoring tools to assist in the support and monitoring of processes and resources the Financial Systems Branch (FSB) is responsible for maintaining. FMO will review features and mechanisms available in the tool(s) and make a selection of the three. The selection will then initiate the process of performing the proper procedures for certification and accreditation requirements. The tool will not integrate with any other systems or applications at CDC for the purpose of utilizing that systemâ€™s data. The tool will be used to monitor existing virtual server resources, availability, services and scheduled processes. The technological scope of the tool will entail monitoring MS OS 2008 application and IIS web servers, other 3rd party software services and scheduled processes, and Microsoft SQL Server database processes. We require the use of the LAB for the sole purpose of adequately assessing the 3rd party tools while reducing risk and cost of introducing the tools into the CDC environment. This will reduce cost and effort.  ', '', 'Roberta (Bobbi) Beach (OCOO/FMO/FSB)', 'Branch Chief', 'Randy Rutledge (OCOO/FMO/FSB)', 'Team Lead', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(134, 132, 'The National Chronic Kidney Disease surveillance system provides resources documenting the public health burden of diabetes and its complications in the United States.  The Kidney Disease Indicators is a user-friendly web-based tool designed to support surveillance, epidemiology, and program evaluation activities.  \r\nThe overall business objectives of the application are to ensure that the community interested in promoting Kidney health has access to data that monitors the prevalence of Kidney Disease, risk factors for developing Kidney Disease, treatment of Kidney Disease, and complications associated with Kidney Disease. \r\nâ€¢	the data is presented in useful and accessible formats \r\nâ€¢	the data is useful for planning/enhancing, implementing and evaluating kidney disease promotion/prevention programs in state and community settings\r\nThe Chronic Kidney Disease surveillance system was developed by the Applications Delivery Team group within Northrop Grumman.   Additional testing is needed by external partners.   The CDC customer has requested that we make the application available to all external partners so they can review the application and data prior to deploying the application to production.  We would like to utilize the CDC lab to provide external partners visibility into the application for validation and demonstration, and allow them to update the lab site with their updated application for transition back into the CDC.\r\n', '', 'Desmond Williams', 'Government Monitor', 'Nilka Rios Burrows', 'Business Steward', 'William Scott', 'Delivery Team Manager', 'Claudia Hudson', 'Project Manager', 'Epidemiologists, Economists and Statisticians with an interest in Kidney disease data for the U.S. p', 'External Stakeholder', 'Policymakers seeking findings from earlier studies for long-term comparisons', 'External Stakeholder', '', '', '', ''),
(148, 146, 'Goals\r\nDemonstrate utility of web based study design and data management features supported by the REDCap application. \r\nChallenges\r\nNone, REDCap is a mature application\r\nOpportunities\r\nPossible path towards supporting  state of the art data management in international collaborative research, and linking data management with mobile data capture. \r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(149, 147, 'We are process an extremely complex Bayesian model examining the association between intake of folic acid and the risk of neural tube intake. The analysis will be done using the WinBugs free analysis software which is currently cleared at Level III for CDC use. The analysis is based on over 250,000 de-identified participants and current overwhelms NCBDDDâ€™s computing capabilities\r\n\r\nThe goal is to use Bayesian methods to estimate the potential association between estimates foliate red blood cell dose and the risk of neural tube defect using data from a very large cohort study conducted in two provinces in China in the early 1990s. The data is de-identified and is comprised only od the following elements: months taking foliate supplement, province (North or south) and neural tube defect outcome (yes, no).', 'Owen Devine	Senior Statistician, modeler NCBDDD\r\nKrista Crider	Epidemiologist, Geneticist, NCBDDD\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(136, 134, 'This feasibility project will devise, demonstrate and document the processes for developing mobile research/informational applications suitable for gathering research information from currently hard-to-reach populations of workers, such as long-haul truck drivers and healthcare providers working irregular shift hours. Increasingly mobile workforces, such as the aforementioned, make it vital that we develop the tools and capability to meet the worker where they are and at the lowest possible cost. Therefore, the purpose of this project is to develop the capability to support mobile application development and deployment to economically meet research needs in a timely fashion.\r\n\r\nThe lab can provide unique services, experience and economies of process that are not available to our group.\r\n-have the app store coming on line.\r\n-have a process for procuring testing platform devices.\r\n-have experience with the CDC pitfalls for deployment/development\r\n', '', 'NIOSH Research Scientists', 'user', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(143, 141, '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(137, 135, 'We would like to gain access to mobile and reader hardware to preview and text CDC/NIOSH materials on these devices.  Specifically we are seeking to gain access to an iPad, Amazon Fire and Android phone.', '', 'CDC/NIOSH/EID', 'Data supplier', 'CDC/NIOSH/OD', 'Governing body', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(139, 137, 'The CDC Global AIDS Program (GAP) Data Management Team (DMT) will be providing support for PEPFAR countries in terms of fundamental data and spatial data management to support HIV AIDS free generation goals over the next 2 years.   Data management  will require a test space to explore Knowledge Management software such as MS Sharepoint and other Knowledge Management / portal software for team space management.', '', 'CDC GAP Data Mgt Team', 'CDC Global AIDS Program', 'CDC ESIB Branch.', 'CDC Global AIDS Program', 'CDC CGH Center staff', 'CDC Global AIDS Program', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(145, 143, 'The proof of concept is to show that NCHS DOQS (Customized version of IBIS-PH) can produce reports that derive from summarization of complex data for which its basis is public-use data.  The objective is that these reports allow for readers to have access to comprehensible information on vital statistical data in a compact publication.  A goal of NCHS DOQS is to provide the public with capabilities to define queries that yield results from real time processing and not from pre-tabulated data.  The challenge is to test the feasibility of NCHS DOQS being able to process thousands of variable crossings in deriving at statistical analysis upon request in a reasonable time period. \r\n\r\nThe COT Software, IBIS-PH, which is an open source that runs on Apache/Tomcat (also open source) with a SAS server backend.  Because IBIS-PH is Open source software, it is necessary to utilize this lab to prototype different configurations and develop project capabilities for the purpose of determining feasibilities and possible associated risks while operating inside the CDC network.\r\n', '', 'Current: DHCS', 'User, sponsor, data supplier, future system maintenance support team', 'Future: All NCHS Data Divisions', 'User, and data supplier', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'R1: The project success is defined by the feasibility to port the system to CDC computing environment, sustaining a stable computing environment, and the ability to incorporate customized features that meet stakeholdersâ€™ needs. \r\n\r\nR2: This project will be measured by the usersâ€™ acceptability and working system functions as defined by usersâ€™ specifications. \r\n\r\nR3: Because data used in this system is public use, the potential impact is marginal.  The possible impact will emerge from misinterpretation or misrepresentation of system reporting results.\r\n\r\n', '', '', ''),
(140, 138, 'The LRN is a coordinated network of state and local public health, federal and international laboratories that can respond to bioterrorism, chemical terrorism and other public health threats. The LRN results Messenger application, a software application developed by CDC provides LRN laboratories with the ability to manage and share laboratory data for LRN-related testing. It is a self contained web application that is installed locally and runs under the control of each laboratory.', 'LRN Partners=\r\nâ€¢	Department of Health and Human Services\r\nâ€¢	Food and Drug Administration\r\nâ€¢	US Department of Agriculture\r\nâ€¢	Department of Defense\r\nâ€¢	Department of Energy\r\nâ€¢	Department of Homeland Security\r\nâ€¢	Federal Bureau of Investigation\r\nâ€¢	Environmental Protection Agency\r\nâ€¢	Association of Public Health Laboratories \r\nâ€¢	American Society for Microbiology\r\n', 'CDC LRN Program', 'Business owner and user', 'LRN member laboratories (state and local public health, veterinary, federal, military, and internati', 'Users', 'Department of Homeland Security BioWatch Program', 'User', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(141, 139, 'We intend to acquire several smartphone devices and tablets to conduct a laboratory-based assessment to compare the functionality and accuracy of sound measurement applications using our type I and type II sound level meters and dosimeters.  We will use our noise generation algorithms to simulate various noise environments in our acoustic test laboratory at NIOSH Taft facility to document and characterize the response of these devices.  In the second phase, we will document the response in real-life noisy environments.  One of the major issues for all of these applications is the appropriate method for calibration.  We intend to generate accuracy curves for each device and for each application and provide users (and future developers) with the tools to address proper calibration techniques for these applications.  \r\n\r\nIn an effort to test all available iOS, Android, and Windows-based devices, we anticipate that we need to test the microphones, sound processing capabilities, and sound measurements applications for the most recent and popular mobile devices in use today.  The following is a proposed list of unlocked devices needed for the project (no service commitment needed):\r\n1.	Apple iPhone 3GS (iOS)\r\n2.	Apple iPhone 4S (iOS)\r\n3.	Apple iPad3 (iOS)\r\n4.	Samsung Galaxy SIII i9300 (Android)\r\n5.	Samsung Galaxy Note N7000 (Android)\r\n6.	HTC One X S720E (Android)\r\n7.	Samsung Focus I917 (Windows)\r\n8.	Motorola XT910 Droid Razr (Windows)\r\n9.	Nokia Lumia 900 (Windows)\r\n\r\nWe intend to continue to test new devices and new applications as they become available, we anticipate that we will only acquire devices in the future at a rate of 1-2 per year based on updated hardware (especially microphone and sound processing circuitry) and popularity of use.  \r\n\r\nList of Sound Measurement applications:\r\n1.	AudioTools 4.3 (iOS) â€“ Studio Six Digital\r\n2.	SoundMeter/dB (iOS) â€“ Faber Acoustical\r\n3.	Decibel Meter Pro (iOS) â€“ Performance Audio\r\n4.	Sound Level (iOS) â€“ Darren Gates\r\n5.	NoiseLevel (iOS) â€“ KBMSoft Aps\r\n6.	SoundMeter (Android) â€“ Smart Tools Co.\r\n7.	Sound Meter (Android) â€“ Kumar Mettu\r\n8.	deciBel Pro(Android) â€“ BSB Mobile Solutions\r\n9.	SoundTools (Android) â€“ Breinovation\r\n10.	Noise Meter (iOS, Android, Windows) â€“ European Environment Agency\r\n11.	Noise Exposure (Android) â€“ Arbetsmiljoverket\r\n12.	dB Level (Android) â€“ Tandem Media Group\r\n13.	NoiseTube (iOS, Android) â€“ NoiseTube\r\n14.	Noise Meter (Windows) â€“ Impact_2011\r\n15.	Sound Sentry (Windows) â€“ Xochl Media\r\n16.	Decibel Meter Pro (Windows) â€“ JOJO Mobile\r\n', '', 'Occupational safety and health professionals, industrial hygienists, public health officials, and pu', 'Recipient of information and report on efficacy of mobile sound measurement apps â€“ Collect occupat', 'Application developers', 'Recipient of information â€“ Improve application accuracy', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(142, 140, 'This project creates a knowledge base for public health reporters to access reporting requirements, reporting criteria, lab criteria and case criteria.  The reporting rules will be managed by public health jurisdictions and will be specific to those jurisdictions.  The project will evaluate existing components to determine those that will comprise the knowledge base.  The project will assess gaps in functionality and recommend how to fill them.  The main challenge, that can be satisfied by the R&D Lab, is to create an environment where the various components can co-live for evaluation and to prototype integration.  ', '', 'Jim Buehler (OSELS/PHSIPO)', 'Sponsor', 'Kathy Gallagher (OSELS/PHSIPO)', 'Sponsor', 'Bob Pinner (OID/NCEZID)', 'Sponsor', 'Laura Conn (OSELS/PHSIPO)', 'Project Lead', 'Public Health Jurisdictions ', 'Knowledge Managers & Viewers', 'Public Health Reporters', 'Users', 'Stakeholders:\r\nJim Buehler (OSELS/PHSIPO)	Sponsor\r\nKathy Gallagher (OSELS/PHSIPO)	Sponsor\r\nBob Pinner (OID/NCEZID)	Sponsor\r\nLaura Conn (OSELS/PHSIPO)	Project Lead\r\nPublic Health Jurisdictions 	Knowledge Managers & Viewers\r\nPublic Health Reporters	Users\r\nPublic Health Reporter Systems	Technology Users\r\n', '', '', ''),
(146, 144, 'The Division of STD Prevention will soon update one section of the STD Treatment Guidelines. The updates will be published as part of MMWR on August 10, 2012. Because we are only making a modification and not revising the entire document, weâ€™d like to make some minor changes to the existing iBook (http://www.cdc.gov/std/2010-ebook.htm). \r\nDue to firewalls and software restrictions, our web developer cannot access Sigil, the tool used to create the iBook, from his CDC desktop. We are asking permission for remote access to the lab in order to make these updates.\r\n', '', 'Physicians', 'user', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(152, 150, 'The Mobile Framework Services is the server-side components that support CDC Mobile Framework iOS and Android (and soon Windows 8) mobile applications.  The server-side components are responsible for transforming (the Transformation Engine) and delivering (the Update Service) publically available CDC content into a format used by the mobile apps.  The transformations provide, among other things, optimizations and normalization of content (e.g., fixing URLs to be app relative, extracting images/tables to separate content items, etc.).  The delivery mechanism takes into account providing incremental updates to mobile apps based on just the content that has changed since the last time the mobile app has synchronized its content.\r\nThe Transformation Engine is a Java console application that is run as a Windows Service via a .NET application that is used to simplify installation/configuration of the Java app.  The Update Service is a Java web application that run under JBoss and has an IIS front-end to mirror the production CDC architecture.\r\nThe Informatics Lab is an important part of being able to test these applications prior to submissions as it provides an external-facing test bed that can be access by mobile devices provided to (or already owned by) CDC and HHS OPDIV content owners.  The testing cycle associated with configuring the content and its presentation for use within the mobile applications is an iterative, rapid response activity that requires an environment that allows for these types of content changes.\r\n', 'Carol Crawford, OADC/DNEM/EMB	Business Steward\r\nFred Smith, OADC/DNEM/EMB	Technical Steward\r\nTed Hsieh, FDA/CTP	HHS OPDIV Customer (FDA)\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
