(171, 169, 'We intend to acquire several smartphone devices and tablets to conduct a laboratory-based assessment to compare the functionality and accuracy of sound measurement applications using our type I and type II sound level meters and dosimeters.  We will use our noise generation algorithms to simulate various noise environments in our acoustic test laboratory at NIOSH Taft facility to document and characterize the response of these devices.  In the second phase, we will document the response in real-life noisy environments.  One of the major issues for all of these applications is the appropriate method for calibration.  We intend to generate accuracy curves for each device and for each application and provide users (and future developers) with the tools to address proper calibration techniques for these applications.  \r\n\r\nIn an effort to test all available iOS, Android, and Windows-based devices, we anticipate that we need to test the microphones, sound processing capabilities, and sound measurements applications for the most recent and popular mobile devices in use today.  The following is a proposed list of unlocked devices needed for the project (no service commitment needed):\r\n1.	Apple iPhone 3GS (iOS)\r\n2.	Apple iPhone 4S (iOS)\r\n3.	Apple iPad3 (iOS)\r\n4.	Samsung Galaxy SIII i9300 (Android)\r\n5.	Samsung Galaxy Note N7000 (Android)\r\n6.	HTC One X S720E (Android)\r\n7.	Samsung Focus I917 (Windows)\r\n8.	Motorola XT910 Droid Razr (Windows)\r\n9.	Nokia Lumia 900 (Windows)\r\n\r\nWe intend to continue to test new devices and new applications as they become available, we anticipate that we will only acquire devices in the future at a rate of 1-2 per year based on updated hardware (especially microphone and sound processing circuitry) and popularity of use.  \r\n\r\nList of Sound Measurement applications:\r\n1.	AudioTools 4.3 (iOS) â€“ Studio Six Digital\r\n2.	SoundMeter/dB (iOS) â€“ Faber Acoustical\r\n3.	Decibel Meter Pro (iOS) â€“ Performance Audio\r\n4.	Sound Level (iOS) â€“ Darren Gates\r\n5.	NoiseLevel (iOS) â€“ KBMSoft Aps\r\n6.	SoundMeter (Android) â€“ Smart Tools Co.\r\n7.	Sound Meter (Android) â€“ Kumar Mettu\r\n8.	deciBel Pro(Android) â€“ BSB Mobile Solutions\r\n9.	SoundTools (Android) â€“ Breinovation\r\n10.	Noise Meter (iOS, Android, Windows) â€“ European Environment Agency\r\n11.	Noise Exposure (Android) â€“ Arbetsmiljoverket\r\n12.	dB Level (Android) â€“ Tandem Media Group\r\n13.	NoiseTube (iOS, Android) â€“ NoiseTube\r\n14.	Noise Meter (Windows) â€“ Impact_2011\r\n15.	Sound Sentry (Windows) â€“ Xochl Media\r\n16.	Decibel Meter Pro (Windows) â€“ JOJO Mobile\r\n', '', 'Occupational safety and health professionals, industrial hygienists, public health officials, and pu', 'Recipient of information and report on efficacy of mobile sound measurement apps â€“ Collect occupat', 'Application developers', 'Recipient of information â€“ Improve application accuracy', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(154, 152, 'BioSense program is planning to use OpenMRS Notifiable Condition Detector (NCD) module to analyze test / synthetic laboratory data coming to Biosense  program via HL7 2.5.1 messages. NCD helps to analyze the coded and free text laboratory data and will not use actual BioSense data for testing in the lab . Initial scope of this project is to implement the openMRS in the lab and evaluate the NCD module for analyzing the LabCorp HL7 messages.  BioSense program wants to use the OpenMRS NCD module to associate the BioSense lab data with reportable conditions.\r\nNCD module will be analyzed first using the vocabulary tables present in NCD. Later, Reportable Condition Mapping Table (RCMT) will be imported into NCD module for analyzing the BioSense lab data.\r\nIf this works for BioSense program, NCD would be integrated in BioSense 2.0 cloud environment as a web service. OpenMRS is an opensource project, which allows us to modify the application based upon public health needs. One of the goal is to make OpenMRS NCD module as a web service. \r\nIf NCD works for BioSense program, then this could be used by State Public Health Agencies for analyzing the ELR data at the jurisdiction level.\r\n', '', 'BioSense program', 'Analyze BioSense lab data', 'CDC Vocabulary Team (DISO)', 'Provide the business rules and coded vocabulary (RCMT) for mapping the lab data to reportable condit', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(155, 153, 'To create a non-functional mock-up of the LEI Informatics Self-Assessment tool using the Balsamiq software. This would help in fine tuning the requirements.\r\nDepending on resources and time, the activity may incorporate a deployment of the assessment tool on either SharePoint, or on the Web. The anticipated deployment environment is outside CDC so the lab is a good fit for testing how the solution would behave. It provides an opportunity to test a solution for small scale analysis of specialized data that primarily rests with the institutions, but still has the option of sharing with external partners.\r\n', '', 'OSELS/LSPPPO', 'Project sponsor', 'APHL', 'Stakeholder', 'State and Local PHLs', 'Users and data supplier.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(156, 154, 'Copied from InfoAid request:\r\n\r\nNeeds: \r\nThis informatics project needs a database programmer and a web programmer/developer to be in charge of the technical specifications as well as product development. Because of logistics constraints (Fellow availability, and ability of EOC to deploy Fellows on the field), potentially 2 fellows can be involved with this project who can both be involved with design/specification development (to be done remotely) and their in-field deployment be staggered to accommodate their availability and the project timeline. \r\n\r\nBackground: \r\nPakistan is committed in its efforts against polio. The government has enforced Augmented National Emergency Action Plan for Polio; WHO and other UN agencies are assisting Gov of Pakistan in its efforts; major donors such as Rotary and Gates Foundation are also instrumental. \r\n\r\nData Management: At the federal level, the WHO Country Office handles the polio data electronically received from Provinces, merges, checks error, runs analyses and produces reports, using at least 6 different systems: 1) SDMS (SIA Data Management System) = pre-Campaign data and process data, access-based system; 2) IFA (Information For Action) system = AFP surveillance data  â€“ Epi-info DOS-based system; 3) Laboratory results information system â€“ Lab IFA Epi Info (Dos version); 4) Environmental Surveillance - MS Excel; 5) Mobile campaign data â€“ Epi Surveyor-based. All systems are running smoothly now, however, Infomration from one system has to be manually related to that from other systems and many robust analyses canâ€™t be currently done because of the data residing in different systems. Advantage:  A common identifier EPID number to be used for an integrated information system to streamline the data management processes and combine the various systems into one integrated system with various modules.  \r\n\r\nGoals:\r\nDevelop an online dashboard for senior leadership and other high-level stakeholders on the bases of the "results monitoring framework". The idea is that the dashboard can provide routine as well as ad-hoc information at different levels (country, province, District/region, Union Council (if feasible) depending on stakeholder interest.\r\n\r\nNeed for IRDU resources:\r\nâ€¢	Prototype development using open source tools\r\nâ€¢	Project management and collaboration resources', '', 'CDC Emergency Operations Center', 'Coordination with Pakistan Polio Program and WHO', 'CDC NCIRD Global Immunization Division', 'Subject matter expertise in polio eradication', 'WHO - Pakistan Polio Program', 'Beneficiaries of InfoAid', 'PHIFP', 'Project management, consultation and service', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(157, 155, 'The Division of HealthCare Quality Promotion is developing a new surveillance definition for Ventilator Associated Events (VAE).  Because the protocol is somewhat complex, I am developing a web based calculator that steps through the protocol and assists in making the various VAE determinations based on data entered.  The calculator is written using jQuery and is entirely client based.  No data is ever sent to the server.  Nor is there any PII data entered.  ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(159, 157, 'The goal of this effort is to develop a pilot demonstration that illustrates how well current (and near-term) automated HIE capabilities can be used to monitor and analyze the efficiency of preventive care interventions; collect valuable lessons learned; provide real-world feedback to the standards bodies involved; and lay the groundwork for a preventive care community of providers, HIEs, and public health organizations. \r\n\r\nThis project will be recruiting a Health Information Exchange (HIE), and collecting ABCs-associated data (e.g., population-at-risk, receipt of clinical preventive services, and longer-term associated health outcomes in the HIE population) through NwHIN and Meaningful Use capabilities to evaluate the effectiveness of these programs. In addition to the ABCâ€™s, the project would like to collect diabetes measures, thus the ABCDâ€™s. The project team has selected a set of clinical quality measures (CQMâ€™s) from the stage 1 Meaningful Use criteria. The CDC subset of measures can be made available upon request. \r\n\r\nThe project has created a technical steering committee dedicated to the creation of a reference implementation of a tool compliant to Stage 2 MU biosurveillance criteria specifications. In addition to transmitting CQMs, the team would like to identify an HIE capable of supporting a two week pilot dedicated to collecting biosurveillance data. The HIE would be invited to participate in the Steering Committee, but the creation of the tool would be the responsibility of the CDC project team. \r\n\r\nSeveral of these early products may be reused in future public health initiatives with HIEs.  This effort has been supported by the National Center for Chronic Disease Prevention and Health Promotion within CDC (Dr. Mary George). \r\n\r\nSCHIEPPH is the name of DISOâ€™s contract, States Communities HIE Preventative Public Health. SCHIEPPH contract ends in July 2013 and Taha/Keiran will work to either archive or transition access to appropriate parties.\r\n', '', 'Taha Kass-Hout', 'COTR', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(160, 158, 'This request facilitates security awareness training for remote resources who do not have access to the CDC campus. ', '', 'OSELS', 'Training participants', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(163, 161, 'We have developed a Mobile web app (GBS) which will be released in the next couple of weeks. Simultaneously, we have started developing native app for Android market and iOS .\r\nWe are about 80% done with the Native App. I have been able to test on Android SDK which can be installed on Windows. However, I need a Mac for testing the app against iOS SDK. Windows PC doesnâ€™t allow iOS SDK.\r\n', '', 'NCIRD, Pediatricians, Obstetricians', 'Health care personnel, Doctors', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Document the end product and ensure that all the client agree on the final result. Regularly measure progress and performance and modify the project to achieve the success criteria.\r\nThe cornerstones of GBS prevention are prenatal screening of all pregnant women for GBS colonization, intrapartum antibiotic prophylaxis (IAP) for colonized women, and assessment of neonates at high risk for EOGBS disease. More than half of the hospitals surveyed had policies that were not consistent with CDC GBS guidelines. This tool helps providers receive the specific guidance needed for a particular patient scenario ,it allows users to input patient characteristics such as gestational age and GBS culture results and receive specific recommendations based on the 2010 CDC GBS guidelines.\r\nThis type of tool has become an increasingly popular and useful way for physicians to receive desired information on recommendations.\r\n', ''),
(161, 159, 'The purpose of this project is to evaluate the utility of text mining functionalities offered by PolyAnalyst 6 as eliciting knowledge from unstructured text represents a major technological challenge.  We would like to analyze policy documents (Meaningful Use) to generate actionable knowledge from mixtures of text and structured data.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'users:\r\n\r\nMelvin Crum	mcrum@cdc.gov\r\n\r\nNinad Mishra	nmishra@cdc.gov\r\n\r\n', '', '', ''),
(162, 160, 'The purpose of this pilot is to implement an instance of the LexEVS terminology server platform and validate if LexEVS and the LexGrid schema supports the NHSN vocabulary and terminology needs. The instance will also allow NHSN program to test the usability elements of the lexEVS admin and user modules and advice the future steps in adopting the solution. The effort will also validate if the CTS2 implementation by LexEVS is sufficient to communicate with external and internal NHSN users.\r\n\r\nIn addition, this server will also serve as testing platform for the Ventilator Associate Event calculator implemented by Dr. Barry Rhodes.\r\n', '', 'NHSN Program', 'protocol implementer, data recipient,', 'Infection Control Software Implementers (EMR, ICS etc)', 'user, data supplier', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(164, 162, 'CGH personnel provide a constant stream of Level III requests that require different Window desktop OS (XP Pro, Win 7), that are not connected to the CDC LAN.  The intent of this request is to provide an environment where we can load the candidate application and, using the SCAP Compliance Checker, determine if the application meets the USGCB standard.', '', 'Members of CGH', 'All roles ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(166, 164, 'Be Smoke-Free (BSF) is a Facebook system designed to allow friends and family members of smokers to send personal messages encouraging the smokers of any age to stop smoking. Users are encouraged to send messages via Facebook or e-mail to the smokers in their life to remind them of the events they may miss if they continue to smoke â€“ or enjoy if they quit. The system provides step-by-step instructions for creating the message with either personal or stock images, smoking related facts, and online cessation resources.', '', 'Jackie Mathis', 'Project Manager ', 'Patti Seikus', 'Business Steward', 'Mahshid Amini', 'Technical Steward', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'The project success will be based on deploying an application that will allow the users to use the Be Smoke-Free system without encountering application errors. As well as, reducing the burden and confusion that exist in the current application,  The measures and metrics that will be used to determine the project success will be based on the Top-Level Heuristic UX Review clarification and understanding presented by OSH.\r\nThe Be Smoke-Free system will have the following public health/business impacts:\r\nâ€¢	Increased dissemination of tailored cessation resources through the use of a social media approach that is different than a standard web application or online pamphlet-ware online.\r\nâ€¢	Increased attempts to quit smoking by smokers of all ages through the use of personalization of public health messages which has been shown to positively impact the success of quit attempts.\r\n', 'The project success will be based on deploying an application that will allow the users to use the Be Smoke-Free system without encountering application errors. As well as, reducing the burden and confusion that exist in the current application,  The measures and metrics that will be used to determine the project success will be based on the Top-Level Heuristic UX Review clarification and understanding presented by OSH.\r\nThe Be Smoke-Free system will have the following public health/business impacts:\r\nâ€¢	Increased dissemination of tailored cessation resources through the use of a social media approach that is different than a standard web application or online pamphlet-ware online.\r\nâ€¢	Increased attempts to quit smoking by smokers of all ages through the use of personalization of public health messages which has been shown to positively impact the success of quit attempts.\r\n'),
(165, 163, 'New R&D Lab engagement:  IRDA staff is currenly working with FMO staff to test out the development of an eBook version of the CDC Congressional Justificiation (CJ) document.   The eBook will be â€‹optimized to work on both the iPhone/iPad (iOS) and Android platforms - and would provide significant advantages (features and customization) over the existing PDF format.\r\n\r\nNeed to see the quality and performance of this ePub- given the size of the document, and the numbers of graphs and images.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(167, 165, 'The goal of this project is to develop a subset of Epi Infoâ€™s data collection, analysis and statistical functionality for the iOS environment. This will allow epidemiologists to load their Epi Info forms onto iPads and perform epidemiologic investigations during public health emergencies, particularly when Internet and network connectivity is disrupted. The labâ€™s Apple MacOS environment will facilitate development of this iOS app.  ', '', 'CDC OD', 'Requester', 'STLT', 'User', 'Global Health', 'User', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Bringing the functionality of this product up to par with its sister product, Epi Info Mobile Companion for Android, would be considered a success. This will provide base data collection and analysis functionality to public health professionals while enabling ongoing improvements and feature additions as resources become available. '),
(168, 166, 'Recently the CDC Electronic Media Branch (EMB) QA and Project Management Team proposed a new structure for the Tech and Innovation Teams due to the considerable changes in project number, size, complexity, and visibility and resource management.  The goal of restructuring was to continue providing quality products on schedule to EMB internal and external customers. \r\nAs a result of project process analysis, the team identified some areas that needed improvements in order to achieve specific goals, such as cross-project resource and time management, standardized method and project controls, impact analysis, daily operation reports, visibility of day-to-day project activities, helpdesk ticketing, and results, etc.\r\nThe lab would provide us an environment to download an evaluation copy of JIRA and configure Atlassian JIRA and various plugins that could be integrated with this tool to address some of the issues identified as needed improvements. \r\n', 'Fred Smith	Governing Body / Report Recipient\r\nDawn Fama	User / Data Supplier\r\nRandall Kittredge	User / Data Supplier\r\nNadezhda Lipskaya	User / Data Supplier / Report Recipient\r\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Demonstrate the advantages/features with JIRA vs SharePoint'),
(169, 167, 'The Surveillance and Data Management Branch (SDMB) is in the process of training its employees on SQL Server 2008. The employees have taken an introduction to SQL Server 2008 class (December 4-6, 2012). Now, the employees need a development environment to practice the skills learned. Also, this development environment will help employees prepare for the advanced class scheduled for the first week of March. ', 'OID/NCHHSTP/DSTDP/SDMB	Data Management', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'This project will be defined as successful if the majority of the employees practice the skills learned in the Introduction to SQL Server 2008 class in preparation for the Advanced SQL Server 2008 class in March.', '', '', 'This project will be defined as successful if the majority of the employees practice the skills learned in the Introduction to SQL Server 2008 class in preparation for the Advanced SQL Server 2008 class in March.'),
