(174, 172, 'Goals\r\nSetting up a sandbox to explore mobile data collection tools, specifically the use case where the workflow corresponds to directly replacing paper based instruments\r\n\r\nChallenges\r\nSecurity and privacy requirements for electronic data capture solutions on mobile devices\r\n\r\nOpportunities\r\nSuccess in this area may result in approved contemporary solutions for data collection in international work\r\n', '', 'Xenophon Santas', 'xms1@cdc.gov', 'Eric-Jan Manders', 'ejmanders@cdc.gov', 'James Kariuki', 'wmo7@cdc.gov', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', 'Success is achieved when we can demonstrate utility of the tools and applications and can demonstrate that security/privacy requirements can be met'),
(176, 174, 'Key features of mobile app:\r\n\r\n1.  Find by condition (substance)\r\n2.  Every substance has 3 sub-options of content  - Profile, ToxGuide (if available), and FAQ,\r\n3.  Profile = 178 documents  - each ranging from 100-600 pages.. some pages scanned in, others not.\r\n4.  ToxGuide is 2 pages\r\n5.  FAQ is usually 2 pages as well\r\n6.  To create iPad Prototype\r\n7.  key is to manage massive amount of content ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
